#-Function--msginfo
  Function: msginfo
      Desc: output an information message, with option to write to systemd journal.
  Synopsis: msginfo [log] string [string ...]
          : 	'log'	if specified, write log entry to journal info. 'log' is positional,
          : #X					:	and must appear before the strings to be printed.
          : if verbose() enabled, write string/s to stdout.
   Example: msginfo "Sir. There's something I think you should know."
#-Function--msginfo-----------------------------------------------------------
